<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-05-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-05-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="287" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d287">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">124.84/64: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi>
                                    (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-05-04">May 4, 1936</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>146. Your 246, May 4, midnight, to Murray. You should inform the
                                Foreign Office at once that this Government accepts with
                                appreciation the offer to instruct the British Legation at Addis
                                Ababa to send a convoy to evacuate the entire American Legation.</p>
                            <p>Engert is being so informed.</p>
                            <p>Please keep the Department fully and promptly informed of all further
                                developments.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>